      "content": "that river metaphor makes sense i guess but it still feels like there's something hidden in there. like i'm paying hundreds of dollars but only a tiny bit goes to the actual loan. can u show me the math for one month? like if i owe 30k at 6% interest how much of my $300 payment is actually hitting the principal vs just paying off interest?",
