      "content": "wait i think your math is a bit off or something. if the interest is 6% per year, shouldn't i divide that by 12 for the monthly rate? if i use the whole 6% for one month the interest would be way higher than my actual payment. anyway, why does it feel like the interest is \"eating\" my payment before it even touches the debt? it feels almost predatory or like there are hidden things happening that i can't see in the numbers.",
